    37â†’## Executive Summary
    38â†’
    39â†’HexTrackr is a comprehensive vulnerability management platform that centralizes security data from multiple vulnerability scanners (Tenable, Cisco, Qualys), processes weekly CSV imports up to 100MB containing 25,000+ vulnerability records, provides real-time analytics dashboards with <500ms response times, and integrates with ServiceNow and Hexagon ticketing systems to streamline the complete vulnerability lifecycle. The system enables

security analysts and network administrators to efficiently track, analyze, and remediate vulnerabilities across their infrastructure through automated workflows, intelligent deduplication with 80% confidence threshold, and comprehensive audit trails for compliance reporting.
    40â†’
    41â†’---
    42â†’
    43â†’## Primary Use Cases
    44â†’
    45â†’### 1. Weekly Vulnerability Import and Deduplication
    46â†’
    47â†’Security teams need to efficiently process weekly 100MB CSV vulnerability reports containing 25,000+ records, automatically detect vendor formats, and prevent duplicate entries through intelligent matching with 80% confidence threshold.
    48â†’
    49â†’### 2. Real-Time Progress Tracking and Analytics
    50â†’
    51â†’Management needs visibility into import progress via WebSocket communication with 100ms throttling, vulnerability trends with <200ms chart renders, device security scoring, and remediation progress across the organization.
    52â†’
    53â†’### 3. Multi-System Ticket

Orchestration
    54â†’
    55â†’Network administrators need to coordinate remediation activities between ServiceNow and Hexagon systems while maintaining comprehensive documentation, markdown generation, and ZIP export packages with audit trails.
    56â†’
    57â†’### 4. High-Performance Data Management
    58â†’
    59â†’Organizations need to support 50 concurrent users, process 5,911 records per second, maintain <500ms table loads, handle rate limiting at 1000 requests per 15 minutes, and ensure data integrity with backup/restore capabilities.
    60â†’
    61â†’## User Scenarios & Testing
    62â†’
    63â†’### Security Analyst Weekly Import Workflow
    64â†’
    65â†’**Primary Scenario:**
    66â†’
    67â†’1. Analyst receives weekly 100MB CSV export from cyber team (Tenable/Cisco/Qualys data)
    68â†’2. Import CSV through drag-and-drop interface with real-time progress tracking
    69â†’3. System automatically detects vendor format and processes at 5,911 records/second
    70â†’4. Intelligent deduplication prevents

duplicates with 80% confidence threshold
    71â†’5. Review imported vulnerabilities using table (<500ms load) and card views
    72â†’6. Filter and sort 25,000+ vulnerabilities to identify critical devices
    73â†’7. Analyze device-specific vulnerability profiles and security scores
    74â†’8. Track vulnerability lifecycle (active, fixed, resurfaced) across weeks
    75â†’9. Navigate to ticket creation for high-priority remediation items
    76â†’
    77â†’**Testing Requirements:**
    78â†’
    79â†’- CSV import completes 100MB files successfully with progress feedback
    80â†’- Vendor format detection works for Tenable, Cisco, Qualys formats
    81â†’- Deduplication achieves 80% accuracy threshold
    82â†’- Week-to-week tracking shows fixed and resurfaced vulnerabilities
    83â†’- Table loads complete in <500ms for 25,000+ records
    84â†’- Filtering and sorting function correctly across all fields
    85â†’- Device details modal displays complete vulnerability information
    86â†’- WebSocket progress updates at

100ms intervals
    87â†’
    88â†’### Network Administrator Ticket Orchestration
    89â†’
    90â†’**Primary Scenario:**
    91â†’
    92â†’1. Create new ticket for site remediation in HexTrackr
    93â†’2. Add devices requiring rebooting in correct sequence
    94â†’3. Generate markdown documentation from ticket data
    95â†’4. Copy markdown to ServiceNow change request system
    96â†’5. Return to HexTrackr and paste ServiceNow ticket information
    97â†’6. Update markdown with both system ticket numbers
    98â†’7. Copy updated markdown to Hexagon ticketing system
    99â†’8. Generate Hexagon ticket and capture ticket number
   100â†’9. Update HexTrackr with Hexagon ticket number
   101â†’10. Export ZIP package with complete documentation
   102â†’11. Attach ZIP to ServiceNow incident
   103â†’12. Email documentation to supervisors using templates
   104â†’
   105â†’**Testing Requirements:**
   106â†’
   107â†’- Ticket creation accepts device information correctly
   108â†’- Markdown generation includes all necessary

details
   109â†’- Copy/paste workflow preserves formatting between systems
   110â†’- ZIP export includes all required documentation
   111â†’- Email templates format correctly
   112â†’- Audit trail captures all ticket state changes
   113â†’- Ticket relationships maintained across systems
   114â†’
   115â†’### Manager Dashboard Analytics Review
   116â†’
   117â†’**Primary Scenario:**
   118â†’
   119â†’1. Access main dashboard with <200ms chart render times
   120â†’2. Review vulnerability statistics for 25,000+ records
   121â†’3. Examine trend analysis showing security posture changes
   122â†’4. Monitor device-centric security scoring calculations
   123â†’5. Generate executive reports from dashboard data
   124â†’6. Export data in multiple formats for presentations
   125â†’7. Monitor system health with 50 concurrent users
   126â†’8. Review processing status and performance metrics
   127â†’
   128â†’**Testing Requirements:**
   129â†’

display historical data accurately

   136â†’
   137â†’### Compliance Officer Audit and Reporting
   138â†’
   139â†’**Primary Scenario:**
   140â†’
   141â†’1. Access comprehensive audit trails for all changes
   142â†’2. Review data retention policies for compliance
   143â†’3. Demonstrate vulnerability lifecycle tracking
   144â†’4. Export compliance reports for CISA/TSA requirements

   158â†’## User Stories
   159â†’
   160â†’**As a Security Analyst:**
   161â†’
   162â†’- I need to import 100MB weekly vulnerability scans containing 25,000+ records so that I can track our security posture efficiently
   163â†’- I need intelligent deduplication with 80% accuracy so that I can prevent duplicate entries and maintain data quality
   164â†’- I need to track vulnerability lifecycle states (active, fixed, resurfaced) so that I can demonstrate remediation progress
   165â†’- I need real-time progress tracking via WebSocket so that I can monitor large import operations
   166â†’- I need <500ms table load times so that I can quickly analyze vulnerability data
   167â†’- I need device-centric views so that I can prioritize remediation by affected systems
   168â†’
   169â†’**As a Network Administrator:**
   170â†’
   171â†’- I need to orchestrate tickets between ServiceNow and Hexagon so that I

can coordinate remediation efficiently
   172â†’- I need markdown generation from vulnerability data so that I can create standardized documentation

   174â†’- I need customizable templates so that I can standardize communication across teams
   175â†’- I need audit trails for ticket changes so that I can maintain compliance records
   176â†’- I need to track ticket relationships so that I can manage complex remediation workflows
   177â†’
   178â†’**As an IT Manager:**
   179â†’
   180â†’- I need dashboard analytics with <200ms render times so that I can quickly assess security posture
   181â†’- I need support for 50 concurrent users so that my entire team can access the system
   182â†’- I need trend analysis over time so that I can report improvements to executives
   183â†’- I need device security scoring so that I can identify high-risk systems
   184â†’- I need multiple export formats so that I can create various report

types
   185â†’- I need performance monitoring so that I can ensure system availability
   186â†’
   187â†’**As a Compliance Officer:**
   188â†’
   189â†’- I need comprehensive audit trails so that I can demonstrate compliance with regulations
   190â†’- I need data retention policies so that I can meet CISA/TSA/government requirements
   191â†’- I need backup and restore capabilities so that I can ensure disaster recovery
   192â†’- I need security protections (path traversal, rate limiting) so that I can prevent vulnerabilities
   193â†’- I need export capabilities so that I can provide evidence for audits
   194â†’- I need vulnerability lifecycle tracking so that I can show continuous improvement
   195â†’
   196â†’### Functional Requirements
   197â†’
   198â†’**Import and Processing Performance:**
   199â†’
   200â†’- System must process CSV files up to 100MB containing 25,000+ vulnerability records
   201â†’- System must achieve 5,911 records per second processing throughput
   202â†’- System must automatically detect

vendor formats (Tenable, Cisco, Qualys)

   205â†’- System must track vulnerability lifecycle states across weekly imports
   206â†’
   207â†’**User Interface Performance:**
   208â†’
   209â†’- System must achieve <500ms table load times for 25,000+ records
   210â†’- System must render charts and analytics in <200ms
   211â†’- System must support page transitions in <100ms
   212â†’- System must handle 50 concurrent users without degradation
   213â†’- System must provide responsive design for desktop and mobile
   214â†’- System must offer both table and card-based data views
   215â†’
   216â†’**Ticket Integration:**
   217â†’
   218â†’- System must orchestrate tickets between ServiceNow and Hexagon
   219â†’- System must generate markdown documentation from vulnerability data
   220â†’- System must create ZIP export packages with remediation

instructions
   221â†’- System must maintain ticket relationships and status across systems
   222â†’- System must support customizable templates for communication
   223â†’- System must preserve formatting in copy/paste workflows
   224â†’
   225â†’**Infrastructure and Security:**
   226â†’
   227â†’- System must deploy via Docker container on port 8989
   228â†’- System must enforce rate limiting at 1000 requests per 15 minutes
   229â†’- System must use database with concurrent access support
   230â†’- System must maintain 4 core tables with 52 performance indexes
   231â†’- System must prevent path traversal and file upload vulnerabilities
   232â†’- System must provide secure storage for API credentials
   233â†’
   234â†’**Data Management:**
   235â†’
   236â†’- System must support weekly import cycles with vendor detection
   237â†’- System must provide backup and restore for disaster recovery
   238â†’- System must maintain comprehensive audit trails for all changes
   239â†’- System must enforce data retention

policies for compliance
   240â†’- System must export data in multiple formats for reporting
   241â†’- System must ensure data integrity during all operations
   242â†’
   243â†’**Testing and Validation:**
   244â†’
   245â†’- System must support end-to-end testing of user workflows
   246â†’- System must provide manual validation checkpoints
   247â†’- System must meet performance benchmarks for all operations
   248â†’- System must validate CSV imports for all vendor formats
   249â†’- System must verify ticket orchestration workflows
   250â†’- System must track week-to-week vulnerability changes
   251â†’
   252â†’## Key Entities
   253â†’
   254â†’### Vulnerabilities
   255â†’
   256â†’- Central entity with CVE identifiers, severity scores, and vendor metadata
   257â†’- Lifecycle states: active, fixed, resurfaced
   258â†’- Confidence scoring for deduplication matching
   259â†’- Relationships with devices and remediation tickets
   260â†’- Historical tracking across weekly imports
   261â†’
   262â†’### Devices
   263â†’

264â†’- Network infrastructure components with hostname and location

   266â†’- Grouped by criticality for remediation prioritization
   267â†’- Relationship tracking with tickets and vulnerabilities
   268â†’

   287â†’The system is currently in production (Version 1.0.12) with:

experience serving security teams daily
